paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: Extracted genetic variant information for the KCNH2 gene, including penetrance data.

functional_data.summary: The common SNP rs4725982, 3′ of KCNH2, was associated with QT interval (+0.09 SD/minor allele, MAF=0.22, P = 6×10−9). A second SNP at KCNH2, rs2968864 was associated with shorter QT interval duration for increasing minor allele count, but did not reach genome-wide significance.

variants.additional_notes: Variants rs4725982 and rs2968864 were associated with QT interval but specific patient data was not provided.
key_quotes: The common SNP rs4725982, 3′ of KCNH2, was associated with QT interval (+0.09 SD/minor allele, MAF=0.22, P = 6×10−9).
A second SNP at KCNH2, rs2968864 was associated with shorter QT interval duration for increasing minor allele count, but did not reach our pre-specified genome-wide significance threshold.

extraction_metadata.notes: No individual patient data was available for the KCNH2 variants.
